11
00:01:10,312 --> 00:01:13,293
Now, let's talk about What is FOMOA AI?.

12
00:01:13,293 --> 00:01:19,447
FOMOA is a free AI search engine optimised for Indian users and Indian context.

13
00:01:19,447 --> 00:01:27,752
Instead of bolting an "India mode" onto a global model, it was built from the ground up around three things global tools get wrong:

14
00:01:27,752 --> 00:01:34,146
Language — Indians search in Hindi, English, and a constant code-mix of both ("Hinglish").

15
00:01:34,146 --> 00:01:38,389
FOMOA detects the language automatically and answers in kind..

16
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:51,670
Sources — it draws on 150+ authoritative Indian sources (government portals, regulators, major Indian publications) instead of treating a random blog as equal to an official notification..

17
00:01:51,670 --> 00:01:59,951
Format — it understands the Indian number system (lakhs, crores), Indian dates, and the structure of Indian government schemes..

18
00:01:59,951 --> 00:02:06,406
You can use it as a normal web search assistant, or — if you are a developer — through an OpenAI-compatible API.

19
00:02:06,406 --> 00:02:11,418
I cover the developer side in depth in the companion guide, FOMOA for Developers.

20
00:02:11,418 --> 00:02:14,134
Moving on to Why an India-First Engine Matters.

21
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:19,170
Here is where global AI models consistently fail Indian users:

22
00:02:19,170 --> 00:02:21,262
1. The Indian number system.

23
00:02:21,262 --> 00:02:24,675
"12 lakh" is 1,200,000.

24
00:02:24,675 --> 00:02:27,704
"2.5 crore" is 25,000,000.

25
00:02:27,704 --> 00:02:35,300
Global models frequently misread these, and a single misread digit destroys a tax, loan, or salary answer.

26
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:39,350
FOMOA treats lakh/crore as first-class units.

27
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:42,007
2. Source credibility blindness.

28
00:02:42,007 --> 00:02:49,903
Most AI search treats Wikipedia, a government circular, and an SEO content farm as roughly equal text.

29
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:53,365
For "what documents do I need for a passport," that is dangerous.

30
00:02:53,365 --> 00:02:58,076
FOMOA scores sources explicitly (more on the ranking system below).

31
00:02:58,076 --> 00:03:00,817
3. Hindi and Hinglish queries.

32
00:03:00,817 --> 00:03:06,045
Roughly half of India's internet users are more comfortable in Hindi than English.

33
00:03:06,045 --> 00:03:13,377
A query like "PM Kisan ka paisa kab aayega" should just work — no translation, no language toggle.

34
00:03:13,377 --> 00:03:15,841
4. Government scheme navigation.

35
00:03:15,841 --> 00:03:21,225
India runs 100+ central schemes and 1000+ state schemes.

36
00:03:21,225 --> 00:03:27,764
Finding the one you qualify for, with the right documents and the official application link, is genuinely hard.

37
00:03:27,764 --> 00:03:36,682
This is one of FOMOA's strongest use cases — covered in detail in FOMOA vs Exa.ai and India Use-Cases.

38
00:03:36,682 --> 00:03:40,204
Next up: FOMOA's Core Features in 2026.

39
00:03:40,204 --> 00:03:42,403
Native Hindi and Hinglish support.

40
00:03:42,403 --> 00:03:46,310
FOMOA handles three modes with zero manual switching:

41
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:51,466
Pure Hindi (शुद्ध हिंदी) — full Devanagari queries and answers..

42
00:03:51,466 --> 00:03:56,009
Hinglish — "Mujhe ek accha SIP plan batao for long term.".

43
00:03:56,009 --> 00:03:59,290
Code-mixed — a sentence that swaps scripts mid-way..

44
00:03:59,290 --> 00:04:09,158
It auto-detects the language and, importantly, expands Hindi queries to also search high-quality English sources, then answers back in the user's language.

45
00:04:09,158 --> 00:04:18,161
On internal Hindi factual-query benchmarks this reached around 89% accuracy — a number that comes directly from how the model was trained (below).

46
00:04:18,161 --> 00:04:21,442
150+ Indian authoritative sources.

47
00:04:21,434 --> 00:04:34,220
FOMOA maintains a curated index of Indian government domains, regulators, and reputable publications, with Indian government domains (.gov.in, .nic.in) getting automatic trust.

48
00:04:34,220 --> 00:04:39,617
So a scheme question is answered from the actual ministry page, not a third-party aggregator.

49
00:04:39,617 --> 00:04:42,141
Indian number and format understanding.

50
00:04:42,141 --> 00:04:49,268
Lakhs, crores, Indian financial-year dates, GST/PAN context — handled natively.

51
00:04:49,268 --> 00:04:57,045
This sounds small until you watch a global model turn "₹2.5 crore" into "$2.5 million."

52
00:04:57,045 --> 00:04:58,811
Government scheme navigator.

53
00:04:58,811 --> 00:05:10,073
Ask in plain language ("schemes for women entrepreneurs in Maharashtra") and get eligibility, required documents, benefits, and the official application link — sourced from official portals.

54
00:05:10,073 --> 00:05:11,420
Deep research mode.

55
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:20,494
For harder questions, FOMOA can follow leads across multiple "hops," detect conflicts between sources, and synthesise a cited report.

56
00:05:20,494 --> 00:05:27,477
There are three depths — quick (~5s), normal (~15s), and deep (~60s).

57
00:05:27,477 --> 00:05:30,783
The mechanics are explained in FOMOA for Developers.

58
00:05:30,783 --> 00:05:32,177
Real-time information.

59
00:05:32,177 --> 00:05:41,612
FOMOA pulls fresh data from its Indian source set rather than relying only on a training snapshot, so exam dates, scheme deadlines, and prices stay current.

60
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:44,352
Free, OpenAI-compatible API.

61
00:05:44,352 --> 00:05:52,201
Developers can point the standard OpenAI SDK at FOMOA by changing the base_url — no rewrite required.

62
00:05:52,201 --> 00:05:56,672
This is the feature that makes FOMOA interesting beyond consumer search.

63
00:05:56,672 --> 00:06:00,734
Let's explore How FOMOA Ranks Results: The 4-Signal System.

64
00:06:00,734 --> 00:06:08,487
The single most important thing separating FOMOA from "ask a chatbot" is that it ranks sources explicitly before answering.

65
00:06:08,487 --> 00:06:10,771
Four signals combine into a score:

66
00:06:10,771 --> 00:06:13,018
Signal, Weight, What it measures.

67
00:06:13,018 --> 00:06:18,343
Semantic relevance, 50%, How well the source actually answers the query.

68
00:06:18,343 --> 00:06:26,263
Source credibility, 25%, Authority of the domain (gov/regulator/established publisher → high).

69
00:06:26,263 --> 00:06:30,807
Content freshness, 20%, How recent the information is.

70
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:35,975
Domain expertise, 5%, Topical match between source and query.

71
00:06:35,975 --> 00:06:38,319
A couple of things make this practical:

72
00:06:38,319 --> 00:06:41,480
Indian government domains get automatic trust.

73
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:45,674
A gov.in notification outranks a blog summarising it..

74
00:06:45,674 --> 00:06:47,513
Weighting is query-adaptive.

75
00:06:47,513 --> 00:06:56,359
For "latest NEET 2026 date," freshness matters more; for "what is compound interest," credibility and relevance dominate..

76
00:06:56,359 --> 00:06:59,052
Conflicts are surfaced, not hidden.

77
00:06:59,052 --> 00:07:07,045
When sources disagree, FOMOA shows the disagreement and the more authoritative source, instead of silently picking one..

78
00:07:07,045 --> 00:07:16,107
This is the same instinct behind good engineering: don't treat all inputs as equal — score them, weight them, and make the decision auditable.

79
00:07:16,107 --> 00:07:23,246
