80
00:07:23,246 --> 00:07:28,655
Now let's look at How FOMOA Was Trained (86,000 India-Centric Samples).

81
00:07:28,655 --> 00:07:34,172
FOMOA's India fluency is not a prompt trick — it is baked into the model weights.

82
00:07:34,172 --> 00:07:36,311
The training approach, briefly:

83
00:07:36,311 --> 00:07:40,674
Base model: Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct.

84
00:07:40,674 --> 00:07:49,557
A 7B model was a deliberate choice — large enough to reason well, small enough to serve cheaply and stay free for users..

85
00:07:49,557 --> 00:07:59,713
Method: QLoRA fine-tuning (4-bit quantised base + low-rank adapters), which makes fine-tuning a 7B model feasible on modest hardware..

86
00:07:59,713 --> 00:08:04,208
Training data (≈86,000 samples):.

87
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:15,266
56,760 Hindi/Hinglish samples (about 65% of the mix) — this is why Hindi works natively rather than via translation..

88
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:19,653
20,000 analytical-reasoning samples..

89
00:08:19,653 --> 00:08:23,234
10,000 diverse-knowledge samples..

90
00:08:23,234 --> 00:08:26,768
Compute: roughly 113 hours of training..

91
00:08:26,768 --> 00:08:29,869
The key lesson: native beats translated.

92
00:08:29,869 --> 00:08:38,066
A model trained on real Hindi and Hinglish understands idiom and code-mixing in a way that a translate-then-answer pipeline never will.

93
00:08:38,066 --> 00:08:43,078
That is the difference between "technically supports Hindi" and "actually feels Indian."

94
00:08:43,078 --> 00:08:45,879
Now, let's talk about Who FOMOA Is For.

95
00:08:45,866 --> 00:08:52,991
Students — exam dates, syllabus, cutoffs, and scholarships from official NTA/government sources..

96
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:59,301
Professionals — tax, finance, and policy questions answered in Indian units with cited sources..

97
00:08:59,301 --> 00:09:05,599
Business owners — scheme and compliance discovery (MUDRA, GST, registrations)..

98
00:09:05,599 --> 00:09:11,909
General users — government services, healthcare schemes, and everyday queries in their own language..

